0 This film is terrible . The story concerns a woman trying to find out what has happened to her sister . The film struggles with its identity , lurching from Noir / thriller to erotic , with elements of horror thrown in for good measure . The film has a very confused structure , for example with frequent use of flashbacks without tying these into the story . The plot is poorly developed , and the characterisation made it difficult to distinguish between who was who and the part they were playing . Some implausibilities exist in many films , but the scene where the main protagonist willingly accompanies a virtual stranger to his home , then agrees to go upstairs alone ( to where he says she will find a phone ) , minus the gun she had brought with her , to call the Police , was too hard to believe . Some of the cinematography is very poor : we were watching on a 42 " TV so how anyone with a smaller set could work out what was happening in the scenes taken in almost complete darkness is beyond me . Overall , a chaotic mess .
